DOOMIICD.iso
________________________________________________________________________________

Format .............................. ISO/CDR
________________________________________________________________________________

Release Notes
________________________________________________________________________________

Complete retail Doom II CD, including Doom (I).  Burn, mount or extract ISO.
Run install.bat to install Doom II.  For Doom I, change directory doom1cd and
run install.bat.  Play with DOSBox.  Default Sound Blaster AWE, MIDI Port 330
for music and Sound Blaster Port 220, IRQ 7, DMA Channel 1 will work with eight
Sound FX in DOSBox.
________________________________________________________________________________

Basic Installation Help
________________________________________________________________________________

DOSBox installation for burned CD:

- Create a directory on your C: drive called Games
- Run DOSbox
- Insert burned CD in your optical drive
- Type:  mount c c:games
- Type:  mount d d: -t cdrom (Example:  "mount d d: -t cdrom" if D: is the
physical optical drive.  If F: was the physical  drive,
type "mount d f: -t cdrom")
- Type:  d:
- Type:  install
- Continue with installation

DOSBox installation for Windows-mounted CD image:

- Create a directory on your C: drive called Games
- Run DOSbox
- Mount disc image in Windows
- Type:  mount c c:games
- Type:  mount d d: -t cdrom (Example:  "mount d d: -t cdrom" if D: is the
virtual optical drive.  If F: was the virtual drive,
type "mount d f: -t cdrom")
- Type:  d:
- Type:  install
- Continue with installation

DOSBox installation for extracted ISO:

- Create a directory on your C: drive called Games
- Extract ISO to c:gamestemp
- Run DOSbox
- Type:  mount c c:games
- Type:  c:
- Type:  cd temp
- Type:  install
- Continue with installation
- Delete temp folder in c:games afterwards if you no longer need the files
